rComments: Not especially engaging as a lecturer, but friendly and helpful, especially in office hours.

She might be knowledgeable about morphology, but she's a TERRIBLE professor and cannot relay any of her knowledge comprehensibly. Disorganized, forgetful, wanders off topic, seems to have trouble even finishing sentences. Nice woman, but learning much from her is a frustrating challenge. Hard to get a clear answer, making office hours useless too.

absolutely horrible professor.  One of "those" that beleives her age and status at U of T allows her to just quit teaching students all together and act like a complete b****.  Very unhelpful especially when using email.  Prepare for one word answers that don't even explain the concepts, and a terrible grade.

Objectively, the worst professor I have ever had at UofT, including one who didn't speak English.  Not a single handout, no lecture material, inconsistent grading scheme, etc.  Does not take the course seriously, nor seems to mind that undergraduates suffer as a result.  Has ruined Field Methods for me.  I recommend you avoid her.

Alana Johns...what a woman! She's intelligent, charming, funny, and yes, a little aloof, but she's a professor, so I think people should grant her some license to be a little flighty. It comes with the territory.  All in all, a real piece of work!

Spelling mistakes she would debate with Inuit expert in front of us confusing us as to the correct correction- really unprepared, no real formal approach to teaching this interesting language. Undeveloped program. Nice woman but  totally scattered Professor , worst taught class of my year
Not clear in teaching style.  Still, very smart lady.
Very disorganized.  We had to ask her for the assignment due dates and details before she produced them.  Still, very knowledgeable and a keen intellect.
